}}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== "8WRGN64..0A1G" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. :The Flash chip looks like it ''may'' be a MX25L6405DMI-12G (8 MB).
The FCC test report specifies this FCC ID covers both this model and the DIR-610N.
[http://www.dlinkla.com.co/sites/default/files/archivos/DIR-610N+/DIR-610N+_A1_Datasheet_01%28WW%29.pdf Datasheet on '''D-Link Latin America'''] :Additional specifications, per the datasheet, follow... :*Dimensions: 54 mm x 158 mm x 113 mm :*Weight: 164 g
A F0:7D:68 OUI is shown on the FCC EUT's label. It is presumed to be used.
The power adapter shown in the FCC photos is a '''TENPAO''' S003IU0500055 (100-240VAC ~ 50/60 Hz, 150mA -> 5VDC, 550mA).
